## **Filter** {#filter}

For each riding, the top 5 individuals with the highest notability index (from the sum\_visib\_ln\_5criteria column) are selected.

| Rationale | Evidence |
| :---- | :---- |
| Fair geographical representation  | Only 12 ridings without a single person (See [appendix A](#appendix-a)) |
| Manageable sample size for further research | n=491, \~3% of the raw data (N=15565) |

## **Comparison to the raw data** {#comparison-to-the-raw-data}

The filter is broadly representative of the raw data across [categories](#people-by-category), [genders](#heading), and [birth periods](#heading-1).

## **Verification of birthplaces** {#verification-of-birthplaces}

Five columns are added to the Excel sheet for this task:

| Column Name | Explanation |
| :---- | :---- |
| wikipedia | URL to Wikipedia entry for Dashboard |
| source | URL to the source |
| pob mentioned in source | Place of birth mentioned in the source |
| verified? | TRUE: birthplace mentioned matches the raw data CORRECTED: birthplace is edited based on the source BLANK: birthplace cannot be verified; see Notes |
| Notes | Explanation for unverifiable birthplaces |

Overall, birthplaces for 406 individuals were verified. The quality of sources varied, ranging from government websites to unofficial databases. Additionally, 2 serial killers were removed from the dataset.

For CORRECTED birthplaces, the riding name, ID, and coordinates are updated based on the source found. Geographical coordinates for the correct ridings are obtained in two ways:

1. Copying existing coordinates from other individuals in the same riding  
2. Searching for the coordinates in Google Maps, which typically returns the centroid of the area

For unverified individuals:

* Birthplaces for 85 individuals could not be verified due to ambiguous sources (e.g., a source listed “Brampton,” but the city is divided into four ridings). See the full list of unverifiable individuals by riding and category in [Appendix B](#appendix-b).  
* Most unverifiable individuals come from the culture or sports/games categories. The top three occupations among them are actors, hockey players, and politicians.
